<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-353] Locking bug</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-353</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;In org.apache.lucene.store.Lock, line 57 (lucene_1_4_final branch):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (++sleepCount == maxSleepCount)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is incorrect, the sleepCount is incremented before the compare causing it&lt;br/&gt;
throwing the exception with out waiting for at least 1 interation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should be changed instead to:&lt;br/&gt;
if (sleepCount++ == maxSleepCount)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As this is a self-contained simple fix, I am not submitting a patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-John&lt;/p&gt;</description>
